  "tasks": [
    {
      "id": "RQ-0061",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Support allowlisted files beneath ignored directory roots",
      "description": "Parallel ignored-file sync currently cannot copy allowlisted files when Git reports only an ignored parent directory entry instead of the nested file path. Why it matters: repos that ignore a whole directory such as `config/` cannot use `parallel.ignored_file_allowlist` to sync specific files inside that directory, even though the config contract says repo-relative file paths and file globs are supported. Minimal fix: change ignored-path enumeration and matching so preflight and sync can inspect concrete ignored files under ignored directory roots without broadening sync to whole directory trees.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "scan",
        "parallel",
        "sync",
        "gitignored"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/git/status.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/sync/gitignored.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/sync/tests/gitignored.rs",
        "cargo test -p ralph-agent-loop"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: crates/ralph/src/git/status.rs:152-166 :: `ignored_paths` shells out to `git ls-files -i -o --exclude-standard -z --directory`, which collapses ignored directory trees to directory entries instead of nested file paths.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/sync/gitignored.rs:85-123 :: preflight skips entries ending in `/` and fails with `matched no existing gitignored files`, so an allowlist entry cannot match a file hidden behind an ignored parent directory entry.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/sync/gitignored.rs:156-171 :: runtime sync also skips directory entries and only copies `source.is_file()` matches, so the same blind spot persists during actual workspace seeding.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/sync/tests/gitignored.rs:65-141 :: current coverage exercises individually ignored files and same-directory globs, but not a `.gitignore` rule like `config/` plus an allowlist entry such as `config/local.json`.",
        "command: tmp=$(mktemp -d) && cd \"$tmp\" && git init -q && printf 'config/\\n' > .gitignore && mkdir -p config && echo '{}' > config/local.json && printf 'with --directory: ' && git ls-files -i -o --exclude-standard -z --directory | perl -0ne 'print join(q(,), grep { length } split(/\\0/, $_))' && printf '\\nwithout --directory: ' && git ls-files -i -o --exclude-standard -z | perl -0ne 'print join(q(,), grep { length } split(/\\0/, $_))' && printf '\\n' :: output was `with --directory: config/` and `without --directory: config/local.json`."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Adjust ignored-path discovery or downstream expansion so allowlist evaluation can see concrete ignored files inside ignored directories while still refusing broad directory mirroring.",
        "Add regression coverage for both preflight and `sync_ralph_state` using a repo that ignores `config/` but allowlists `config/local.json` and a narrow file glob under that directory.",
        "Verify by running targeted Rust tests for the new ignored-directory-root cases and `make agent-ci`, then confirm the nested allowlisted file is copied into the worker workspace."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "scan finding",
      "created_at": "2026-04-29T00:48:35Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-29T00:48:35Z",
      "depends_on": [],
      "blocks": [],
      "relates_to": [],
      "custom_fields": {
        "scan_agent": "scan-general"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "RQ-0062",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Block ignored-file sync from following repo-escaping symlinks",
      "description": "Parallel ignored-file sync currently treats gitignored symlinks as regular files and copies their resolved content into worker workspaces without checking whether the target stays inside the repository. Why it matters: a trusted allowlist or default ignored-file sync entry can exfiltrate arbitrary local machine files into worker clones and downstream runner prompts. Minimal fix: canonicalize matched ignored files during preflight and sync, reject symlinks whose resolved target escapes the repo root, and add regression coverage for both escaping and safe in-repo cases.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "scan",
        "parallel",
        "sync",
        "gitignored",
        "security"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/sync/gitignored.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/sync/common.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/sync/tests/gitignored.rs",
        "cargo test -p ralph-agent-loop"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/sync/gitignored.rs:103-114 :: preflight accepts a match as long as `source.is_dir()` is false and `source.is_file()` is true, which is also true for symlinks pointing to regular files outside the repo.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/sync/gitignored.rs:165-171 :: runtime sync repeats the same `source.is_file()` gate before copying the matched path into the worker workspace.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/sync/common.rs:24-33 :: `sync_file_if_exists` blindly calls `fs::copy(source, target)` and does not constrain symlink targets to the repo root.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/sync/tests/gitignored.rs:25-260 :: current ignored-file sync tests do not cover symlinked allowlist entries or repo-escape checks.",
        "command: tmp=$(mktemp -d) && outside=$(mktemp) && printf 'secret' > \"$outside\" && cd \"$tmp\" && git init -q && printf 'secret-link\\n' > .gitignore && ln -s \"$outside\" secret-link && { git ls-files -i -o --exclude-standard -z --directory | perl -0ne 'print qq([).join(q(],[), grep { length } split(/\\0/, $_)).qq(]\\n)'; printf 'islink=%s isfile=%s real=%s\\n' \"$(test -L secret-link && echo yes || echo no)\" \"$(test -f secret-link && echo yes || echo no)\" \"$(python3 -c 'import os; print(os.path.realpath(\"secret-link\"))')\"; } :: output showed `[secret-link]` plus `islink=yes isfile=yes`, proving the current path classification would admit an ignored symlink."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Introduce a canonical-path safety check for ignored-file matches and reject any symlink or resolved file path that escapes `repo_root` before sync begins.",
        "Add regression tests for an ignored symlink to an external file and for an allowed ignored file that remains inside the repo.",
        "Verify by running the focused ignored-file sync test suite and `make agent-ci`, then confirm the external-symlink case fails preflight with an explicit safety error."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "scan finding",
      "created_at": "2026-04-29T00:48:35Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-29T00:48:35Z",
      "depends_on": [],
      "blocks": [],
